@startuml
autonumber
skinparam Style strictuml

actor "User (Admin)" as Admin
participant "System" as Sys
database "Database" as DB

Admin -> Sys: Navigates to Roles section
activate Sys
Sys -> Sys: Renders Roles Administration table
Sys -> Sys: Displays toggle switches for each privilege
Sys --> Admin: Show Roles UI

Admin -> Sys: Toggles a specific Privilege switch
Sys -> Sys: Captures change (Privilege ID + New State)
Sys -> DB: Sends update request to server
activate DB

DB -> DB: Updates relationship between Role and Privilege

alt Update Successful? (yes)
    DB --> Sys: Confirms record update
    Sys -> Sys: Displays success notification
    Sys -> Sys: Refreshes toggle state in the UI
    Sys --> Admin: UI updated (Success)
else Update Successful? (no)
    DB --> Sys: Returns error (Conflict/Connection)
    deactivate DB
    Sys -> Sys: Displays error message
    Sys -> Sys: Reverts toggle switch to previous state
    Sys --> Admin: UI reverted (Error)
end

deactivate Sys
@enduml